		<title>By: Fearlezzdreamer</title>
		<link>http://www.alljapaneseallthetime.com/blog/why-are-you-acting-like-a-deadbeat-dad-language-learner#comment-1000507661</link>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Fearlezzdreamer]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 23 Oct 2014 11:12:51 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.alljapaneseallthetime.com/blog/?p=30370#comment-1000507661</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Thanks again for the great post, Khatz.

In my opinion, it doesn&#039;t really matter whether or not anything contradicts against the TMT, I mean that&#039;s what we Ajatteers do. The TMT formule is simply a tool after all, it&#039;s meant to help us, if it gets in the way we might as well screw it, that&#039;s what AJATT is all about, discarding crap that doesn&#039;t help so that we can milk the things that actually DO help.

Considering my Japanese project, I&#039;ve stopped doing my SRS reps the &#039;right&#039; way with timeboxes, under perfect conditions etc. and I only do them when I go to the toilet, am bored in class, have to wait for an appointment and so on. In that way I complete 30-40 % of my daily reps, which isn&#039;t perfect, but it sure as hell adds up. There are some golden days where I actually get 100%, but these days are only occasional, when my SRS items are really interesting and fun, and when I&#039;m in a good mood.
I usually set up 2-3 situational goals a day for my SRS reps, but that&#039;s all I really plan. Anything else I leave to inertia and nature.
  For the rest of the day I just do fun stuff in Japanese, like watching tons of Anime, playing video games, listening to music etc.
Enjoying this journey that we brave people set out onto. :)
Oh and that example with the egg, amazing shizz dawg. 
I really want to meet you one day, for you are the one and only guru that has had such a big and positive effect on my life.  I always look forward to your posts, every fifth day is like a holiday for my, since I can never wait to see what new advice you&#039;ve got in store. I would really love and appreciate it if you could  continue at this pace.

Stay golden and thanks for everything,

-Fearlezz]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Thanks again for the great post, Khatz.</p>
<p>In my opinion, it doesn&#8217;t really matter whether or not anything contradicts against the TMT, I mean that&#8217;s what we Ajatteers do. The TMT formule is simply a tool after all, it&#8217;s meant to help us, if it gets in the way we might as well screw it, that&#8217;s what AJATT is all about, discarding crap that doesn&#8217;t help so that we can milk the things that actually DO help.</p>
<p>Considering my Japanese project, I&#8217;ve stopped doing my SRS reps the &#8216;right&#8217; way with timeboxes, under perfect conditions etc. and I only do them when I go to the toilet, am bored in class, have to wait for an appointment and so on. In that way I complete 30-40 % of my daily reps, which isn&#8217;t perfect, but it sure as hell adds up. There are some golden days where I actually get 100%, but these days are only occasional, when my SRS items are really interesting and fun, and when I&#8217;m in a good mood.<br />
I usually set up 2-3 situational goals a day for my SRS reps, but that&#8217;s all I really plan. Anything else I leave to inertia and nature.<br />
  For the rest of the day I just do fun stuff in Japanese, like watching tons of Anime, playing video games, listening to music etc.<br />
Enjoying this journey that we brave people set out onto. <img src="http://www.alljapaneseallthetime.com/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /><br />
Oh and that example with the egg, amazing shizz dawg.<br />
I really want to meet you one day, for you are the one and only guru that has had such a big and positive effect on my life.  I always look forward to your posts, every fifth day is like a holiday for my, since I can never wait to see what new advice you&#8217;ve got in store. I would really love and appreciate it if you could  continue at this pace.</p>
<p>Stay golden and thanks for everything,</p>
<p>-Fearlezz</p>
